The paper deals with prophet inequalities, which are a topic in game theory and optimization (cs.GT). The paper also discusses matroids and independent sets, which are topics in discrete mathematics and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper proposes algorithms for making decisions based on limited information, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also provides guarantees for the performance of these algorithms, which is a topic in machine learning and theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
